IT Security Technical Specialist
Charterhouse
UAE
Posted on: 1 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Charterhouse is working with a leading brand across the UAE whose headquarters are based in Dubai. Our client is looking to hire an IT Security professional.
You will support the IT operations in handling IT security infrastructure and perform continuous security systems monitoring contributing to the development and maintenance of risk management.
REQUIREMENTS
The successful candidate should have 4 to 8 yearsâ experience in IT security, a related bachelors Degree and industry certifications such as SANS GIAC (GWAPT), CEH alongside Security product certifications.
You will have expert knowledge in handling enterprise network security products including Next generation network/application firewalls, IPS, cryptographic suites and VA tools.
You should have strong knowledge of programming (C++, Perl, Python and Shell) and operating systems on Windows, Linux, HP-UX, Solaris and AIX, ethical hacking will be advantageous.
You should have a proven track record in performing advanced level penetration testing for large scale organizations on web applications and vulnerability identification and remediation.
ABOUT THE COMPANY
During the last ten years, Charterhouse has been operating across Dubai, Abu Dhabi and the GCC Markets. In many ways, we were the recruiter who established and set the standards within the regional recruitment industry benchmarking and innovating the service levels associated to Search and Selection.
Charterhouse understands the dynamics attached to talent acquisition, relationship management and the required service levels within the regional industry. Our heritage is now our main strength as we continue to work within our core markets to deliver key account management and strong contingency recruitment practices to our clients and candidates.
